race.comment: Tricky race to assess with a few of these facing the starter for the first time. POCKET DIAL (7) is one of them but has shown ability winning two recent trials and is sure to be well-educated out of the Gollan barn. Gets Maloney on top to navigate from the sticky draw and a strong showing on debut would not surprise. The well-bred BOOYA BOY (3) (dam was a 3xG2 winner) is another at the races for the first time but his trial form has been very strong and any market moves must be noted. MISHANI VISION (13) hit the frame at Ipswich on debut and will have derived a bunch of benefit from that race day experience. Can feature with natural improvement. LUMINOUS GIRL (14) was well in the betting on debut and where there's smoke there's fire. Keep very safe. STRIKE WEAPON (11) strips fitter second-up from the break and may earn some minor money.
